# 4.6 Advantages of Landsat

The Landsat mission offers numerous advantages.

### High Spatial Resolution

The most important advantage is its high spatial resolution, allowing researchers to distinguish roads, rivers, agricultural fields, buildings, forests, and urban structures.

---

### Long Historical Archive

More than fifty years of continuously collected imagery makes Landsat one of the richest environmental datasets available.

---

### Free Availability

All Landsat imagery can be downloaded freely through the USGS Earth Explorer platform.

---

### Accurate Thermal Measurements

Thermal bands provide reliable estimates of land surface temperature suitable for scientific research.

---

### Multi-Spectral Observations

The eleven spectral bands support a wide range of environmental applications.

---

# 4.7 Limitations of Landsat

Despite its high quality, Landsat also has several limitations.

### Low Temporal Resolution

The satellite revisits the same location approximately every sixteen days.

If cloud cover exists during acquisition, researchers may need to wait another sixteen days.

---

### Limited Daily Monitoring

Unlike MODIS, Landsat cannot provide daily observations.

This limits applications requiring continuous environmental monitoring.

---

### Cloud Contamination

Visible and infrared observations are strongly affected by cloud cover.

Clouds obscure the Earth's surface, reducing the availability of useful imagery.

